// Conditional Access evaluation completeness — flag policies with high "notApplied" volume.
//
// Symptom #5 — Conditional Access evaluation-log incompleteness.
// Source: M365 GCC-Moderate Telemetry & Boundary Assessment, §13.3.5.
// Provenance: inbox/New_FedRAMP_Boundary/M365_GCC-Moderate_Telemetry_and_Boundary_Assessment_External_with_images.docx
// Use: identify CA policies whose scope or exclusion rules are misconfigured, producing high notApplied volume.
//      A policy that almost never applies is usually not enforcing the intended control.
// Note: Entra default 30-day retention without diagnostic settings loses historical CA evaluation;
//       enable AuditLogs + SigninLogs export to Sentinel for retention beyond 30 days.

SigninLogs
| where TimeGenerated > ago(7d)
| where ConditionalAccessStatus == "notApplied"
| summarize NotAppliedCount = count() by ConditionalAccessPolicies = tostring(ConditionalAccessPolicies)
| order by NotAppliedCount desc
| take 20
